@aeslaughter Correct. We use conda-forge's VTK. The only VTK we distribute ourselves is for use by libMesh's VTK support (moose-libmesh-vtk).
@abarun22 Conda does not distribute OpenGL, or mesa (not the mesa we're all thinking. Mesa3d is the product of that error). Conda's VTK simply uses whats available on the machine. If the version available on the machine is too old, you may see a message like that. You are correct in trying to get an older version.
Unfortunately after digging a little, I'm afraid VTK 7.1.1 was only ever built with PyQt 4 (while Peacock requires 5). The errors you are receiving I believe are due to that machine needing a newer implementation of OpenGL and/or Mesa just as the VTK error suggests...
